The key to the &quot;either or&quot; type you&#39;re looking for is called a [union type](http://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/advanced-types.html#union-types). They are defined with the pipe `|` type operator. It basically means _&quot;either this type OR that type&quot;_.

For example:

```ts
type StringOrNumber = string | number;
```

Or:

```ts
type FooOrBar = { foo: string; } | { bar: string; };
```

Or, for your case:

```ts
interface IWithValue {
   value: string;
}

interface IWithValues {
   values: string[];
}

type IValueOrValues = IWithValue | IWithValues;
```

You can find an example in the [typescript playground](https://www.typescriptlang.org/play/?ssl=12&amp;ssc=42&amp;pln=12&amp;pc=1#code/JYOwLgpgTgZghgYwgAgJIHVhgBYDU4A2ArigN4BQyVAboSQFzIDOYUoA5gNzkC+55oSLEQoMWPHQhNkFKslrEpjFmxDsA2gF1ufcmACeAB1H5FAeSimS0gLxpMOKygA+98U6bd+CAPYgWyHCMqE4WHsh2pPKSjADkcLHIPNy+-mDIAEbBoZaStjLRikyM6rEAjLEANMixAExVNQDMsZpJ3EA).

